# Analysis of Group Policy Auditing

## @Configuration Changes
-I enabled success and failure auditing for logon events and object access within Group Policy.

## @Applied Settings
-I configured the relevant GPOs and ensured these settings were propagated across the domain.

## @Log Analysis
-After enabling the audit, I reviewed the security logs for logon/logoff attempts; 4624 (Successful Logon) and 4625 (Failed Logon), and object access.

## @Findings
-This allowed me to confirm that auditing was working properly, ensuring visibility into user and object access events.
